The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 20 October is 85,290 (9,830.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 15 October, there were 3,283 new confirmed cases (378.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 08 October, there were 2,550 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 29% (733 extra cases).
